Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms (logistic regression and neural networks) to predict MOOC student dropout, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also analyzes clickstream data and proxy labels based on students' persistence, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and computer engineering (cs.CE). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze student forum posts, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
